# SDD-100 — parallel-session conflict avoidance.
#
# Three sessions work sovereign-os in parallel, each on its own branch merging to
# main. These append-only "registry" files get a new row per increment, so two
# branches both appending "the next row" would 3-way-conflict on logically
# independent rows. `merge=union` is git's built-in driver that keeps BOTH sides'
# added lines on a merge — no manual conflict, no data loss. Paired with the
# per-session number bands in docs/sdd/README.md (which guarantee distinct SDD /
# E11.M## numbers), so union never produces a duplicate-numbered row.
#
# Only append-only markdown registries belong here — NEVER code or structured
# files where interleaving two edits could corrupt syntax.
docs/sdd/INDEX.md                                        merge=union
docs/standing-directives/2026-05-17-operator-mandate.md  merge=union
docs/src/lifecycle/ongoing.md                           merge=union
docs/observability/dashboards/README.md                 merge=union
docs/decisions.md                                       merge=union
# SDD-980 — the parallel-session registry + the auto-resolver's cross-session
# ledger are append-only too: every session appends its own row / note, so union
# keeps them all. The resolver (scripts/git/sdd_conflict_resolver.py) reads
# SESSIONS.md and appends to RESOLUTION-LOG.md.
docs/sdd/SESSIONS.md                                     merge=union
docs/sdd/RESOLUTION-LOG.md                              merge=union
# SDD-981 — the session message board is one message per row, append-only; union
# keeps every session's messages across merges. Managed by
# scripts/git/session_comms.py.
docs/sdd/MESSAGES.md                                    merge=union
